festival.introText:
We’re delighted to reveal that Dimensions Festival 2023 will take place between the 31st August - 4th September.

Dimensions 2022 far exceeded anything we could have dreamed of… Dancers, DJ's, live performers, record labels, collectives and music fans, we all came together to celebrate our tenth year with one of our favourite parties to date!

In 2023, Dimensions Festival builds on last year’s 10th anniversary with a host of artists, labels and collectives from across the scene, a carefully curated list of champions of the scene, back to back exclusives, label parties, UKG celebrations, debut appearances and much more.
festival.descriptionText: Get more information about Dimensions Festival 2023 including festival tickets, news, reviews and lineups.

reviews.title: All the right dimensions
reviews.body:
Dimensions festival is for all intents and purposes a festival for the heads.

Firstly the lineup is an accurate snapshot of DJs and producers who diligently work to create an inspiring and individual atmosphere and soundscape. Some of these artists receive less recognition than you would think in their usual circles but in Fort Punta Christo its all about the music.

The second key reason Dimensions festival stands head and shoulders above so many other music festivals is the crowd. Passion and highly selective music taste can lead to an air of elitism but I encountered this maybe once the entire weekend. People go to this festival to share their love of music and I came back feeling thoroughly enlightened with my faith in humanity somewhat restored.

My only criticism of this vibrant and exciting festival is the organisation on the ground. Understandably it takes a goliathan effort to co-ordinate so many staff and musicians but I missed 2 or 3 performances I had been looking forward to for months only because the bouncers on the gate had been given incorrect information about what certain passes and wristbands entitled people to see.

In conclusion, go to Dimensions then go and explore Croatia which is truly one of the most beautiful places in Europe. You will not regret it
